Consolidated Script Execution Guide
This script automates the verification of Lab Works 1.1 through 2.3. It interacts with your Docker containers and the ProjectDB database created during the setup phase.
Prerequisites
Ensure you are inside your Ubuntu (WSL2) terminal.
Ensure the directory ~/mssql_labs exists and containers are running (docker ps).
How to Run
Navigate to your project folder:
cd ~/mssql_labs


Create the script file:
nano run_all_labs.sh


Paste the code from the Consolidated Lab Execution Script block above.
Save (Ctrl+O, Enter) and exit (Ctrl+X).
Make the script executable:
chmod +x run_all_labs.sh


Run the script:
./run_all_labs.sh


Expected Results
Lab 1.1-1.2: Console shows server names and confirms the creation of Test and Test_JD databases.
Lab 1.3: You will see sql1 stopping, a file corruption simulation via dd, and a successful database restoration.
Lab 1.4: Logins, users, and roles are created with DENY permissions applied.
Lab 2.1-2.2: SQL Agent jobs, Database Mail components, and Replication distributors are initialized.
Lab 2.3: The script populates 50,000 records into OrderDetails, creates Columnstore indexes, and displays a text-based execution plan.
Technical Notes
The script uses exclusively Latin characters and contains no internal comments to comply with strict console requirements.
It uses the /opt/mssql-tools18/bin/sqlcmd path installed during setup.
